<Defs>
	<AlienRace.ThingDef_AlienRace ParentName="ESCP_BaseRace_MerStandardHead">
		<defName>ESCP_AyleidRace</defName>
		<label>Ayleid</label>
		<description>An elven race, originally exiles, they later built a grand Empire, the first of its kind. Considered to be the most ruthless Mer to ever exist, it is said they turned torture into a form of art. While many Mer races are known for frequently partaking in slavery, the Ayleid practically built their Empire on the backs of slaves.\n\nThe Ayleid Empire was ended after a great slave rebellion. Some Ayleid were allowed to remain, but many fled to other lands, and many more were slaughtered by their usurpers. The Ayleid race has since been considered lost to time, with remnants of their bloodline being found in Bosmer and Bretons. However some Ayleid in far off cities managed to survive.\n\n&lt;color=#E5E54C&gt;Mer Blood&lt;/color&gt;\nPsychic sensitivity is increased by 20%.\nFertility is decreased by 50%.\nBase health scale is decreased by 20%.\nLife expectancy is increased to 300 years.\n\n&lt;color=#E5E54C&gt;The First Empire&lt;/color&gt;\nPsychic sensitivity is increased by an additional 10%.\nGlobal learning factor is increased by 10%.\nSocial impact is increased by 10%.\nAlways has the psychopath trait.</description>
		<modExtensions>
			<li Class="ESCP_RaceTools.RaceProperties">
				<majorRacialGeneToInherit MayRequire="Ludeon.RimWorld.Biotech">ESCP_GeneInheritedBonus_Mer</majorRacialGeneToInherit>
				<minorRacialGeneToInherit MayRequire="Ludeon.RimWorld.Biotech">ESCP_GeneInheritedBonus_Ayleid</minorRacialGeneToInherit>
			</li>
		</modExtensions>
		<statBases>
			<PsychicSensitivity>1.3</PsychicSensitivity>
			<GlobalLearningFactor>1.1</GlobalLearningFactor>
			<SocialImpact>1.1</SocialImpact>
		</statBases>
